Recruitment has begun into the Edo State civil service for the position of agricultural superintendents as part of ongoing reforms of the service. Chairman of the Edo Civil Service Commission, Princess Ekiuwa Inneh in a statement yesterday, urged interested and qualified persons to apply by visiting the civil service commission recruitment portal at csc.edostate.gov.ng and complete the online application.   ‘Give us equal opportunity in governorship…     ‘I’ll revitalise Delta’s moribund industries’     NCDC approves private lab for COVID-19 test in Edo   Inneh assured the people that the recruitment would be free, fair and merit-driven, adding that applicants are not required to make payment to any person or organisation in respect of the recruitment. She said: “All applications must be submitted on or before May 27, 2022. Candidates must not be more than 35 years as at the time of application, and their HND/OND certificates must not be below Lower Credit, while computer/digital literacy will be an added advantage.”